<%# locals: recipe, ingredient, substitute, inventory_items

  Compact "add a substitute" form, one per ingredient row. Each ingredient
  renders its own add form, so — like the ingredient forms — the field ids are
  namespaced (here by the ingredient's dom_id) to stay unique and keep every
  <label for> wired to its own field. The amount/unit are optional: blank means
  the substitute uses the line's own amount.

  Submit natively (not via Turbo), exactly like the ingredient forms: the
  controller's success redirect carries a #ingredient-line-N fragment so the
  reader lands back on the line they were annotating. Turbo Drive resolves the
  post with fetch, strips that fragment from the redirect Location, and resets
  scroll to the top — so under Turbo, adding a substitute to a line far down a
  long recipe throws the reader back to the page top every time. A native submit
  honors the fragment and keeps their place. %>
<%= form_with model: substitute, namespace: dom_id(ingredient, "newsub"),
      url: recipe_ingredient_substitutes_path(recipe, ingredient),
      class: "inline-ingredient-form", data: { turbo: false } do |form| %>
  <% if substitute.errors.any? %>
    <p class="inline-form-error" role="alert"><%= substitute.errors.full_messages.to_sentence %></p>
  <% end %>

  <%= form.label :inventory_item_id, "Substitute item", class: "sr-only" %>
  <%= form.collection_select :inventory_item_id, inventory_items, :id, :name,
        { include_blank: "No item" }, { class: "compact-select" } %>
  <%= form.label :name, "Substitute name", class: "sr-only" %>
  <%= form.text_field :name, class: "compact-input", autocomplete: "off", placeholder: "or name" %>
  <%= form.label :quantity, "Substitute amount", class: "sr-only" %>
  <%= form.number_field :quantity, step: "0.0001", min: "0", class: "compact-input", placeholder: "amt" %>
  <%= form.label :unit, "Substitute unit", class: "sr-only" %>
  <%= form.text_field :unit, class: "compact-input", autocomplete: "off", placeholder: "unit" %>
  <%= form.label :note, "Substitute note", class: "sr-only" %>
  <%= form.text_field :note, class: "compact-input", autocomplete: "off", placeholder: "note" %>
  <%= form.submit "Add substitute", class: "button small" %>
<% end %>
